# ============================================================================
# Signal Champ - Environment Configuration Template
# ============================================================================
# Copy this file to assets/.env and fill in your actual credentials
# Command: cp assets/.env.example assets/.env
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit the actual .env file with real credentials!
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION (Optional - Cloud Features)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Enables: Cloud storage for simulation states, user authentication
#
# How to get credentials:
# 1. Sign up at https://supabase.com
# 2. Create a new project
# 3. Go to Project Settings → API
# 4. Copy the Project URL and anon/public key
#
# Example values:
# SUPABASE_URL=https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6ImFiY2RlZmdoaWprbG1ub3AiLCJyb2xlIjoiYW5vbiIsImlhdCI6MTYzNjUwMDAwMCwiZXhwIjoxOTUyMDc2MDAwfQ.abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz1234567890
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENAI CONFIGURATION (Optional - AI Features)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Enables: AI Agent Panel, intelligent train control suggestions
#
# How to get API key:
# 1. Sign up at https://platform.openai.com
# 2. Go to API Keys section
# 3. Create new secret key
# 4. Copy and paste here
#
# Example value:
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ
#
# Available models (choose one):
# - gpt-3.5-turbo (fastest, cheapest, default)
# - gpt-4 (more capable, slower, more expensive)
# - gpt-4-turbo-preview (balanced)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
OPENAI_API_KEY=
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-3.5-turbo

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SENTRY CONFIGURATION (Optional - Crash Reporting)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Enables: Automatic crash reporting, error tracking, performance monitoring
#
# How to get DSN:
# 1. Sign up at https://sentry.io
# 2. Create a new project (choose Flutter/Dart)
# 3. Go to Project Settings → Client Keys (DSN)
# 4. Copy the DSN URL
#
# Example value:
# SENTRY_DSN=https://abc123def456@o123456.ingest.sentry.io/7654321
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
SENTRY_DSN=

# ============================================================================
# FEATURE MATRIX
# ============================================================================
# Feature                    | Required Variables
# ---------------------------|-------------------------------------------
# Core Railway Simulation    | None (works without .env)
# Cloud Save/Load            | SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# AI Agent Panel             | OPENAI_API_KEY, OPENAI_MODEL (optional)
# Crash Reporting            | SENTRY_DSN
# Connection Debug Panel     | Shows status of all configured services
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# TESTING YOUR CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================
# After filling in credentials:
# 1. Run: flutter pub get
# 2. Run: flutter run
# 3. Check console for: "✅ Environment loaded successfully"
# 4. Open Connection Debug Panel to verify each service
# 5. Test features:
#    - Supabase: Try saving simulation to cloud
#    - OpenAI: Open AI Agent Panel
#    - Sentry: Settings → Crash Reports → Test Crash
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================
# Issue: "✗ .env file NOT found"
# Solution: Ensure file is at assets/.env (not assets/.env.example)
#
# Issue: "SUPABASE_URL loaded:" but no value shown
# Solution: Check that variables have no spaces around = sign
#           Correct:   SUPABASE_URL=https://example.supabase.co
#           Incorrect: SUPABASE_URL = https://example.supabase.co
#
# Issue: "Failed to load OpenAI service"
# Solution: Verify API key is valid and has not expired
#           Check API key at https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
#
# Issue: Variables not loading after editing
# Solution: Hot reload doesn't reload .env file - do full restart:
#           1. Stop the app (Ctrl+C)
#           2. Run: flutter run
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
# ============================================================================
# ✓ DO:
#   - Keep assets/.env in .gitignore
#   - Use separate credentials for dev/staging/production
#   - Rotate API keys regularly
#   - Use environment-specific .env files for team members
#   - Share credentials securely (password manager, encrypted chat)
#
# ✗ DON'T:
#   - Never commit assets/.env to version control
#   - Never share credentials in pull requests or issues
#   - Never use production keys in development
#   - Never hardcode credentials in source code
#   - Never post credentials in screenshots or documentation
# ============================================================================
